member.returns:
A  value indicating that. If ,
both arguments  and  can be used;
otherwise, both arguments should be discards.

member.remarks:
You can use this struct like this:

foreach (short mask in new BitSubsetsGenerator(9, 3))
{
    // Do something to use the mask.
}

remarks.para:
The recommended implementation pattern is:
[ResourceTextFormatter] internal string CellsStr() => Cells.ToString();
You can use the code snippet fitem to create the pattern, whose corresponding file is added into the optional/vssnippets folder. For more information, please open the markdown file README.md (in the optional folder) for more information.

If you want to use the values in the resource documents,
just use the  field  is okay:

using static Sudoku.Resources.MergedResources;

public override string Format => R["TheKeyYouWantToSearch"];
